title: Webb views the ‘cosmic cliffs’ of Carina Nebula
summary: The James Webb Space Telescope’s first image of Carina Nebula, a iconic star-forming cloud of gas and dust 7,600 light-years away, shows previously unseen vistas of young stars thanks to the new observatory’s sharp-eyed infrared vision.

title: La NASA revela las primeras imágenes del telescopio Webb de un universo nunca antes visto
summary: El amanecer de una nueva era en la astronomía ha comenzado mientras el mundo ve por primera vez las capacidades completas del telescopio espacial James Webb de la NASA, en asociación con la Agencia Espacial Europea (ESA, por sus siglas en inglés) y la Agencia Espacial Canadiense (CSA, por sus siglas en inglés).

title: NASA Reveals Webb Telescope’s First Images of Unseen Universe
summary: The dawn of a new era in astronomy has begun as the world gets its first look at the full capabilities of NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope, a partnership with ESA (European Space Agency) and CSA (Canadian Space Agency).

title: SpaceX starts testing its Super Heavy booster, and it’s “not good”
summary: "Going forward, we won’t do a spin start test with all 33 engines at once."

title: NRO space missions mark new level of US-Australia cooperation
summary: Two upcoming Rocket Lab launches for the National Reconnaissance Office will send to orbit classified spy satellites that the U.S. intelligence agency developed jointly with the Australian government.

title: Watch live: Scientists releasing more images from Webb telescope today
summary: Scientists will release additional images and data from the James Webb Space Telescope today, including ultra-sharp infrared views of a star-forming nebula, a colorful cloud of gas around a dying star, a group of distant galaxies, and the first measurement of the composition of a planet around another star. The images will be released at 10:30 a.m. EDT (1430 GMT).

title: BAE Systems delivers jam-resistant GPS receivers to Germany
summary: BAE Systems delivered to Germany advanced GPS M-code receivers.

title: Space cybersecurity firm SpiderOak adds retired general Pawlikowski to its advisory board
summary: Space cybersecurity firm SpiderOak on July 12 announced the appointment of former DoD and military officials to its advisory board.

title: China to target near-Earth object 2020 PN1 for asteroid deflection mission
summary: China has set its sights on near-Earth object 202 PN1 as the target for a combined asteroid deflection and observation test mission due to launch in 2026.

title: BlackSky and Esri unveil tasking through ArcGIS Online
summary: BlackSky Technology unveiled satellite tasking July 12 through Esri’s ArcGIS Online geographic mapping platform.
